	sorted(cons(0, cons(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true

	sorted(cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(s(xts))), nil))) = true

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true

+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) = true
... induction variables of

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true

+++ treating clause
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... induction variables of
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... are:
	xts2:nat
+++ perform INDUCTIVE NARROWING on conjecture 
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... with variable xts2
+++ creating new conjecture
	0 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts2) <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	0 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
... contains a ground negative condition
	true = false
... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded
--- clause
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
+++ added new clause(s)
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... to conjectures

+++ Status of the Inference System
--- Conjectures:
	xts2 <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(xts3)), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(0, insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(0, cons(0, cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
	sorted(insert(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts3)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(s(xts))), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts1))), cons(s(s(s(xts2))), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts1), cons(s(xts2), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
--- Non-orientable hypotheses:
	<empty>
--- Oriented hypotheses:
	sorted(isort(xl)) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts, isort(yts))) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts3, insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts))))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(0, insert(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), nil))) = true

+++ treating clause
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... induction variables of
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... are:
	xts2:nat
+++ perform INDUCTIVE NARROWING on conjecture 
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... with variable xts2
+++ creating new conjecture
	0 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts2) <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	0 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
... contains a ground negative condition
	true = false
... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded
--- clause
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
+++ added new clause(s)
	sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... to conjectures

+++ Status of the Inference System
--- Conjectures:
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	sorted(insert(xts2, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(s(xts3))), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts1), cons(s(xts2), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts3))), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(s(s(0))), cons(s(s(s(xts))), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts1), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
--- Non-orientable hypotheses:
	<empty>
--- Oriented hypotheses:
	sorted(isort(xl)) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts, isort(yts))) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts)))) -> true

	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil))) -> true

	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(0, insert(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true

	sorted(insert(xts3, insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts))))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(0, insert(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(0, insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), nil))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), cons(^f1($n; xts2), nil)))) = true

+++ treating clause
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... induction variables of
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... are:
	xts2:nat
+++ perform INDUCTIVE NARROWING on conjecture 
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... with variable xts2
+++ creating new conjecture
	0 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts2) <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	0 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	true = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(0, cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
... contains a ground negative condition
	true = false
... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded
--- clause
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
+++ added new clause(s)
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... to conjectures

+++ Status of the Inference System
--- Conjectures:
	xts2 <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts3))), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(s(s(0))), cons(s(s(s(xts))), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts1), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(s(0)) = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(s(0)) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(s(s(xts3))), cons(s(s(s(xts2))), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
--- Non-orientable hypotheses:
	<empty>
--- Oriented hypotheses:
	sorted(isort(xl)) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts, isort(yts))) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts)))) -> true

	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts3, insert(xts2, insert(xts1, isort(yts))))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(0, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(0, insert(xts2, cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil))) -> true

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true

	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true

... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(s(0)) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(s(0)) = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), nil))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), cons(^f1($n; xts2), nil)))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(^f1($n; xts2), cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), nil)))) = true

+++ treating clause
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... induction variables of
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... are:
	xts2:nat
	xts1:nat
+++ perform INDUCTIVE NARROWING on conjecture 
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... with variable xts2
+++ creating new conjecture
	0 <= xts = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	0 <= xts = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
... subsumed by an existing conjecture
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded
--- clause
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
+++ added new clause(s)
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... to conjectures

+++ Status of the Inference System
--- Conjectures:
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts1)), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(xts1), cons(s(s(xts2)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(0) = true => sorted(cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(insert(xts2, cons(s(s(s(0))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(xts), nil))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), nil))) = true
	sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(s(0)) = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
	xts2 <= s(s(0)) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
--- Non-orientable hypotheses:
	<empty>
--- Oriented hypotheses:
	sorted(isort(xl)) -> true
	sorted(insert(xts, isort(yts))) -> true

	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(xts1, nil)))) -> true
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(0) = false => sorted(cons(s(0), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(xts2, cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(s(0)) = true => sorted(cons(xts2, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
	xts <= s(s(0)) = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(xts2, cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(xts2), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(insert(xts3, cons(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true
--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(^f1($n; xts1), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), nil))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), cons(^f1($n; xts2), nil)))) = true
	s(xts3) <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(^f1($n; xts2), cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = true => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil)))) = true
	xts3 <= xts2 = false => sorted(insert(xts1, cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts3)), nil)))) = true

+++ treating clause
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing on conjecture
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... induction variables of
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... are:
	xts1:nat
+++ perform INDUCTIVE NARROWING on conjecture 
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... with variable xts1
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts) <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), cons(s(0), nil)))) = true
+++ creating new conjecture
	s(xts2) <= s(xts1) = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	s(xts) <= 0 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), cons(s(0), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	false = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), cons(s(0), nil)))) = true
--- clause
	false = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts)), cons(s(0), nil)))) = true
... contains a ground negative condition
	false = true
... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= s(xts1) = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(xts1), nil)))) -> true
+++ added new clause(s)
	xts2 <= xts1 = true => sorted(cons(s(0), cons(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(xts1)), nil)))) = true
... to conjectures

+++ Status of the Inference System
--- Conjectures:

	sorted(cons(0, cons(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(xts)), nil)))) = true

+++ Presburger system  = {

	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           =

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           =

	xts2 <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(0, cons(s(^f1($n; xts1)), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil)))) = true

	true = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(s(0)), cons(s(s(s(xts))), nil)))) = true
... contains a ground negative condition
	true = false
... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)
--- clause
	s(xts2) <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
... reduced in 1 step to
	sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(s(s(xts2))), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
+++ inductive narrowing succeeded

	xts2 <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) = true
... oriented to rule
	xts <= 0 = false => sorted(cons(s(s(0)), insert(s(s(xts2)), cons(s(s(s(xts1))), nil)))) -> true

... to conjectures

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true

	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           =

--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true

... and is therefore discarded (false => t is always true)

... to conjectures

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           =

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
+++ }

+++ Presburger system  = {

	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
+++ }

+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
	^f283(0; xts) -> xts
	^f283($n283 + 1; xts) -> s(^f283($n283; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true

--- Primal Grammar:
+++ Presburger system  = {
	^f0(0; yts, xts@) -> isort(yts)
	^f0($n0 + 1; yts, xts@) -> insert(xts$n0, ^f0($n0; yts, xts@))
	^f1(0; xts) -> xts
	^f1($n1 + 1; xts) -> s(^f1($n1; xts))
	^f19(0) -> 0
	^f19($n19 + 1) -> s(^f19($n19))
	^f283(0; xts) -> xts
	^f283($n283 + 1; xts) -> s(^f283($n283; xts))
+++ }
+++ Lemma(s)           = 
	sorted(insert(xts$n, ^f0($n; yts, xts@))) = true
	s(xts2) <= xts1 = false => sorted(cons(^f1($n; xts1), cons(s(^f1($n; xts2)), nil))) = true
